cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a multi-task learning-based approach for geometric and semantic scene understanding, specifically depth prediction and semantic scene segmentation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) categories. The approach also utilizes skip connections and adversarial training, which are common techniques in deep learning and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of recurrent networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) but can also be applied to computer vision tasks.
